# Copy this file to `apps/web/.env.local` for local dev.
#
# Why these are needed:
#   Next.js `rewrites()` only proxies HTTP. It cannot proxy WebSocket
#   upgrades for the Socket.IO `/ws` gateway. If the browser connects to
#   the Next dev server on port 3000 for the socket, realtime updates can
#   fail until a manual refresh. `src/lib/env.ts` now falls back to
#   localhost:3001 in dev automatically, but setting this explicitly is
#   recommended for any non-localhost setup.

# Direct origin of the Nest API (used by both REST and Socket.IO).
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3001

# Optional override if the realtime gateway is on a different host than
# the JSON API, for example behind a separate WS-aware reverse proxy.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_REALTIME_ORIGIN=https://realtime.example.com

# Optional: pin the default location id used by the customer and KDS UIs.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DEFAULT_LOCATION_ID=00000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000000
